DOC.brief_summary: This withdrawn study was to assess the safety and efficacy of secukinumab compared to etanercept and placebo in patients who have moderate to severe, chronic, plaque-type psoriasis.
DOC.brief_title: Efficacy and Safety Study of Subcutaneous Secukinumab in Treatment of Subjects With Moderate to Severe Chronic Plaque-type Psoriasis as Compared to Etanercept and Placebo.
DOC.criteria: Chronic plaquetype psoriasis, moderate to severe Candidate for systemic therapy defined as having psoriasis not adequately controlled by: topical treatment, phototherapy and/or previous systemic therapy Forms of psoriasis other than chronic plaquetype Ongoing use of treatments not allowed for psoriasis Other protocoldefined inclusion/exclusion criteria may apply
